ke fibre-optic laryngoscopy and surgical airway double setup | LMA unlikely to be successful in angioedema - move directly to Cricothyrotomy | From Smoke Inhalation protocol: Smoke inhalation - anticipate a difficult airway - see difficult airway protocol. Early airway intervention. SuPara glottic devices unlikely to be successful - move directly to cricothyrotomy | Failed intubation attempts may worsen the airway compromise | From Anaphylaxis protocol: Prepare for an EXTREMELY difficult airway (see Difficult airway & Cricothyrotomy protocols). Avoid airway manipulation if possible. Most skilled person to attempt intubation; failed attempts may worsen compromise | POST-INTUBATION: Confirm ETT placement with bilateral chest rise AND capnography | Secure ETT | Repeat BP and check all vital signs | Chest X-Ray | ABG after 30 minutes | Sedation if required | Attach to ventilator with HME Filter",
